HEADWORD: Subcarbureted
<hw>Sub*car"bu*ret`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>United with, or containing, carbon in less than
the normal proportion.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>subcarburetted</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

